<unittitle>New Maternity Home</unittitle>
<unitid>Hopetoun closed social work file</unitid>
<unitdate>18 April 1903</unitdate>
<abstract>'New Maternity Home' is a digital copy of a photocopy of an item published on 18 April 1903, held in the <span style="font-style:italic">Hopetoun closed social work</span> file at the Salvation Army Heritage Museum WA. A handwritten caption shows the item comes from the <span style="font-style:italic">War Cry</span>. It gives information about the forthcoming opening of a new maternity home for 'upwards of twenty young women and their babes' in Fremantle, which became The Open Door. The item describes the facility.</abstract>
<note label="rights">Salvation Army Heritage Museum WA</note>
</archref>
